{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UrJ3kFJZ3vPRTM8w4HRcmB","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Tasks: m55-d2-parallel-cli-substrate\n2\t\n3\t**Domain wave**: Wave 2 (after D3 ships ratelimit-map.json — calibration only; D2 ships agnostic)\n4\t**Depends on**: D3's `.gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json` (consume-only at recommend-defaults time, NOT imported)\n5\t**Depended on by**: D5 (Track 2 of verify-gate fans out via D2's `runParallel`)\n6\t\n7\t## T1 — Author `parallel-cli-contract.md` v1.0.0 STABLE\n8\t\n9\t**Output**: `.gsd-t/contracts/parallel-cli-contract.md`\n10\t**Acceptance**: API surface (`runParallel({workers, maxConcurrency, failFast?, teeDir?})`), envelope shape, fail-fast + timeout policy, captureSpawn invariant (CLI workers without LLM usage emit `—` not `0`), tee-NDJSON path rule, results sorted by workerId, wallClockMs is orchestrator real-time.\n11\t\n12\t## T2 — Implement `bin/parallel-cli.cjs` library + thin CLI\n13\t\n14\t**Output**: `bin/parallel-cli.cjs`\n15\t**Acceptance**: exports `runParallel(...)`; CLI form `node bin/parallel-cli.cjs --plan plan.json --json` reads plan from file or stdin; honors `maxConcurrency` (no implicit default leak); fail-fast cancels in-flight via SIGTERM → 5s grace → SIGKILL; per-worker timeout same shape as fail-fast cancellation but only for that worker; every spawn flows through `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs::captureSpawn` (CLI workers pass usage envelope `undefined` → renders `—`).\n16\t\n17\t## T3 — Implement `bin/parallel-cli-tee.cjs` helper\n18\t\n19\t**Output**: `bin/parallel-cli-tee.cjs`\n20\t**Acceptance**: exports tee helper that streams stdout/stderr to `{teeDir}/{workerId}.ndjson`; in-memory cap at 1MB per stream then rotates to temp file; returns final path in result.\n21\t\n22\t## T4 — Author `test/m55-d2-parallel-cli.test.js`\n23\t\n24\t**Output**: ≥6 unit tests\n25\t**Acceptance**: happy parallel (3 workers, all succeed), exceeds-cap (5 workers maxConcurrency=2 → throttled), single-fail-fast (cancels siblings), per-worker-timeout (kills only that worker), tee-paths-valid (NDJSON files exist + parse), captureSpawn-invariant (proxy mock confirms wrapper invoked).\n26\t\n27\t## T5 — Implement `bin/m55-substrate-proof.cjs` proof harness\n28\t\n29\t**Output**: `bin/m55-substrate-proof.cjs`\n30\t**Acceptance**: runs N (≥3) deterministic CLI workers (e.g., parallel `tsc --noEmit` against fixture subdirs) sequentially, then via `runParallel`, reports wall-clock ratio. Mirrors `bin/m46-iter-proof.cjs` shape. Reports ≥3× speedup or fails the success-criterion-2 measurement (D5 wave acts on the result).\n31\t\n32\t## T6 — Run substrate proof; record numbers\n33\t\n34\t**Output**: stdout dump appended to `.gsd-t/metrics/m55-substrate-proof.txt` with sequential vs parallel wall-clock + ratio\n35\t**Acceptance**: ratio ≥ 3.0× (success-criterion-2). If <3×, recalibrate (charter rule — do not tag).\n36\t\n37\t## T7 — Run full test suite; confirm zero regressions\n38\t\n39\t**Output**: green `npm test`\n40\t**Acceptance**: baseline 2262/2262 preserved + D2 tests added.\n41\t\n42\t## T8 — Commit D2\n43\t\n44\t**Output**: single commit `feat(m55-d2): parallel-cli substrate + contract STABLE + 3.x speedup proof`\n45\t**Acceptance**: Pre-Commit Gate passes; commit message includes the measured speedup ratio.\n46\t\n47\t## D2 Checkpoint\n48\t\n49\tAfter T1–T8: D2 ready for D5 to import. Substrate proven. Wave 2 → Wave 3 gate met (D5 needs D2 STABLE).\n50\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"59a5fba0-ebf5-4a87-90dc-60296616481a","uuid":"4cc2d486-ee63-4c5f-a962-f2b0efa67c9e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T23:53:51.097Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/domains/m55-d2-parallel-cli-substrate/tasks.md","content":"# Tasks: m55-d2-parallel-cli-substrate\n\n**Domain wave**: Wave 2 (after D3 ships ratelimit-map.json — calibration only; D2 ships agnostic)\n**Depends on**: D3's `.gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json` (consume-only at recommend-defaults time, NOT imported)\n**Depended on by**: D5 (Track 2 of verify-gate fans out via D2's `runParallel`)\n\n## T1 — Author `parallel-cli-contract.md` v1.0.0 STABLE\n\n**Output**: `.gsd-t/contracts/parallel-cli-contract.md`\n**Acceptance**: API surface (`runParallel({workers, maxConcurrency, failFast?, teeDir?})`), envelope shape, fail-fast + timeout policy, captureSpawn invariant (CLI workers without LLM usage emit `—` not `0`), tee-NDJSON path rule, results sorted by workerId, wallClockMs is orchestrator real-time.\n\n## T2 — Implement `bin/parallel-cli.cjs` library + thin CLI\n\n**Output**: `bin/parallel-cli.cjs`\n**Acceptance**: exports `runParallel(...)`; CLI form `node bin/parallel-cli.cjs --plan plan.json --json` reads plan from file or stdin; honors `maxConcurrency` (no implicit default leak); fail-fast cancels in-flight via SIGTERM → 5s grace → SIGKILL; per-worker timeout same shape as fail-fast cancellation but only for that worker; every spawn flows through `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs::captureSpawn` (CLI workers pass usage envelope `undefined` → renders `—`).\n\n## T3 — Implement `bin/parallel-cli-tee.cjs` helper\n\n**Output**: `bin/parallel-cli-tee.cjs`\n**Acceptance**: exports tee helper that streams stdout/stderr to `{teeDir}/{workerId}.ndjson`; in-memory cap at 1MB per stream then rotates to temp file; returns final path in result.\n\n## T4 — Author `test/m55-d2-parallel-cli.test.js`\n\n**Output**: ≥6 unit tests\n**Acceptance**: happy parallel (3 workers, all succeed), exceeds-cap (5 workers maxConcurrency=2 → throttled), single-fail-fast (cancels siblings), per-worker-timeout (kills only that worker), tee-paths-valid (NDJSON files exist + parse), captureSpawn-invariant (proxy mock confirms wrapper invoked).\n\n## T5 — Implement `bin/m55-substrate-proof.cjs` proof harness\n\n**Output**: `bin/m55-substrate-proof.cjs`\n**Acceptance**: runs N (≥3) deterministic CLI workers (e.g., parallel `tsc --noEmit` against fixture sub