lel-cli.cjs`, calibrated by D3); D3 rate-limit probe + empirical map (`bin/gsd-t-ratelimit-probe.cjs` → `.gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json`, ~140k token one-shot spend approved); D4 context-brief generator (`bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs` — renamed to avoid collision with D1's \"preflight\"); D5 two-track verify-gate (state envelope hard-fail + parallel CLI fan-out summary, wire-in to execute Step 1 and verify Step 2, doc ripple). 8 falsifiable success criteria — see milestones table. Charter authored at `.gsd-t/charters/m55-charter.md`. Memory `feedback_no_human_hour_estimates.md` added — drop wall-clock estimates in GSD-T context, use token-spend / rate-limit windows / parallel-domain count instead.\n- 2026-05-09 15:04: [defined] M55 — CLI-Preflight Pattern + Parallel-CLI Substrate + Verify Gate (initial 3-domain scope; SUPERSEDED by 15:30 merge entry above). **Goal**: every GSD-T command runs a deterministic preflight (branch-guard, ports-free, deps-installed, contracts-stable, manifest-fresh, working-tree-state) before spawning work, and parallel fan-out has a single substrate (worker-pool + token-capture wrapping + log-stream tee) instead of ad-hoc `Promise.all([Task,Task,...])` patterns scattered across command files. Verify-gate consumes the preflight envelope and hard-fails on any non-`ok` check. **Why**: recurring pain pattern across M48/M49/M50/M52 — silent-skip regressions caught only by retrofit hooks, ad-hoc parallel patterns that bypass `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs` so token attribution goes blind on fan-out, \"verify\" steps that report PASS when their precondition checks were never actually run. **Scope** (sketch — finalised at partition): D1 preflight library — `bin/cli-preflight.cjs` (pluggable check registry + structured `{ok,checks[],notes[]}` envelope, schema-versioned, zero deps mirroring `bin/parallelism-report.cjs`); D2 parallel-CLI substrate — `bin/parallel-cli.cjs` (N-worker pool, every spawn flows through `captureSpawn`, log-stream tee to per-worker NDJSON, lifecycle/timeout/fail-fast policy, engine-only — does NOT touch command files yet); D3 verify-gate integration — preflight runs before every command spawn via `bin/headless-auto-spawn.cjs` hook + `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` consumes the envelope and hard-fails on any non-`ok` check + `cli-preflight-contract.md` v0.1.0 PROPOSED → v1.0.0 STABLE. **Success criteria**: (1) preflight envelope schema published as STABLE contract; (2) substrate proves ≥3× speedup on a real fan-out scenario via in-tree `bin/m55-substrate-proof.cjs` (measurement, not claim — per `feedback_measure_dont_claim.md`); (3) verify-gate blocks at least 3 distinct preflight failure classes (e.g. wrong-branch, port-conflict, contract-DRAFT) in `e2e/journeys/`-shape tests with corresponding entries in `.gsd-t/journey-manifest.json`; (4) Red Team GRUDGING PASS — ≥5 broken patches, all caught (preflight-skip-on-error, parallel-substrate-bypasses-capture, verify-gate-falsy-true, branch-guard-typo, contract-staleness-ignored); (5) zero regressions on `npm test` (baseline 2262/2262 unit + 1 documented `event-stream.test.js` env-bleed when run in-session under `gsd-t-milestone`); (6) every existing command file remains untouched at the source level (substrate is opt-in via the auto-spawn hook only — adoption is a separate ratchet milestone). **Out of scope**: rewriting all 55 command files to call the substrate directly (separate ratchet milestone candidate, pending M55 ship); cross-project preflight propagation via `gsd-t update-all` (handled in a follow-up); replacing `bin/gsd-t-worker-dispatch.cjs` or `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs` with the substrate (those are unattended-mode supervisors, distinct surface). **Versioning**: minor bump 3.24.10 → 3.25.10 (new feature) on complete-milestone. **Test baseline**: 2262/2262 unit + 1 documented env-bleed failure (this `gsd-t-milestone` run leaks `GSD_T_COMMAND=gsd-t-milestone` into `tests/event-stream.test.js:341` which asserts `command === null`; reproduces cleanly when env vars unset, same pattern as M52 baseline 17:17). Baseline captured this session: `npm test` exit 0 with the documented failure. **Files (planned, finalised at partition)**: `bin/cli-preflight.cjs` (new), `bin/parallel-cli.cjs` (new), `bin/m55-substrate-proof.cjs` (new), `bin/headless-auto-spawn.cjs` (additive preflight hook), `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` (additive envelope consumption), `.gsd-t/contracts/cli-preflight-contract.md` (new v0.1.0 → v1.0.0), `e2e/journeys/preflight-*.spec.ts` (new ≥3 specs), `.gsd-t/journey-manifest.json` (additive entries). **Pre-partition assessment**: medium-complexity (3 file-disjoint domains; substrate work is the riskiest because of token-capture wiring and worker-lifecycle correctness). Recommend standard partition → plan → execute flow. No discussion phase needed — pain pattern and surface are well-understood from M44 (parallelism), M41 (token capture), and M50/M52 (gates). Awaiting `/gsd-t-partition` to decompose into formal domains.\n- 2026-05-08 14:54: [docs] Redrew all 6 workflow diagrams in D2 (light theme 0, ELK layout) replacing the original Mermaid renders. Established consistent visual language: blue rectangles=commands, dashed purple=subagents, red=gates, amber diamonds=decisions, pink hexagon=router, ovals=endpoints, cylinders=artifacts. Added `docs/diagrams/_theme.d2` with shared classes. Sources at `docs/diagrams/NN-name.d2`, SVG renders at `NN-name.svg`, PNG renders at `NN-name-d2.png` (rendered via headless Chrome since D2's native PNG export needs Playwright). Updated `docs/workflow-diagram.md` to point to D2 PNGs and added visual-language legend + regeneration instructions. D2 0.7.1 installed via Homebrew.\n- 2026-05-08 09:19: [docs] Created `docs/workflow-diagram.md` — 6 Mermaid diagrams (top-level entry routing, milestone lifecycle, wave mode, design-to-code pipeline, backlog subsystem, automation/observability/utilities) + phase successor table + auto-spawned subagent table. Derived from `comma