{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018jm7JxsvoqZLQy2pLeVyXU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# GSD-T Progress\n2\t\n3\t## Project: GSD-T Framework (@tekyzinc/gsd-t)\n4\t## Status: ACTIVE — M55 PARTITIONED (5 file-disjoint domains, Wave 1 D1+D3+D4 parallel, Wave 2 D2, Wave 3 D5)\n5\t## Date: 2026-05-09\n6\t## Version: 3.24.10\n7\t\n8\t## Current Milestone\n9\t\n10\tM55 — CLI-Preflight Pattern + Parallel-CLI Substrate + Rate-Limit Map + Context Briefs + Verify Gate (PARTITIONED, MERGED scope)\n11\t\n12\t## Milestones\n13\t\n14\t| # | Milestone | Status | Version | Domains |\n15\t|---|-----------|--------|---------|---------|\n16\t| M55 | CLI-Preflight Pattern + Parallel-CLI Substrate + Rate-Limit Map + Context Briefs + Verify Gate (MERGED scope) | PARTITIONED | 3.24.10 → 3.25.10 (planned) | 5 file-disjoint domains. Wave 1 (parallel): D1+D3+D4. Wave 2: D2. Wave 3: D5. **D1 State-Precondition Library** — `bin/cli-preflight.cjs` (pluggable check registry: branch-guard, ports-free, deps-installed, contracts-stable, manifest-fresh, working-tree-state; deterministic `{ok,checks[],notes[]}` envelope; schema-versioned, zero deps mirroring `bin/parallelism-report.cjs`). **D2 Parallel-CLI Substrate** — `bin/parallel-cli.cjs` (N-worker pool, every spawn flows through `captureSpawn`, log-stream tee to per-worker NDJSON, lifecycle/timeout/fail-fast policy, engine-only — does NOT touch command files yet; concurrency defaults calibrated from D3 empirical map). **D3 Rate-Limit Probe + Empirical Map** — `bin/gsd-t-ratelimit-probe.cjs` (synthetic-worker harness mirroring real GSD-T spawn shape; sweep matrix `{1,2,3,4,5,6,8} workers × {10k,30k,60k,100k} context`; captures per-worker time-to-first-token, 429 count + which worker, total wall-clock, effective ITPM/OTPM; backoff probe + 5-min steady-state probe; real spawns into throwaway worktree; output `.gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json`). **D4 Context-Brief Generator** — `bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs` (single entry: `gsd-t brief --kind {execute|verify|qa|red-team|design-verify|scan} --domain X --json`; produces `.gsd-t/briefs/{spawn-id}.json` ~2k JSON snapshot replacing 30–60k context re-read per worker; `context-brief-contract.md` v1.0.0 — schema, freshness via mtime hash-stamp, fail-open vs fail-closed, idempotent-join rule). **D5 Verify-Gate + Wire-In + Doc Ripple** — `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs` (two-track gate consuming both: state-preflight envelope from D1 hard-fails on non-`ok` checks, AND parallel CLI fan-out via D2 substrate runs typecheck+lint+tests+dead-code+secrets+complexity using off-the-shelf CLIs (tsc/biome/ruff/knip/gitleaks/scc/lizard) with ≤500-token JSON summary; LLM judges summary, never raw output); wire preflight into `gsd-t-execute` Step 1 + verify-gate into `gsd-t-verify` Step 2; update qa/red-team/design-verify subagent prompts with brief-first rule; doc ripple to architecture.md, requirements.md, CLAUDE.md, gsd-t-help.md; Pre-Commit Gate update. **Goal**: lift practical parallelism ceiling from ~3 LLM workers to ~6–10 mixed workers (1 LLM judge + N CLIs) by replacing deterministic LLM work with deterministic CLI work, prove via empirical measurement, and gate every spawn with deterministic state checks. **Why**: pain pattern across M48/M49/M50/M52 — silent-skip regressions caught only by retrofit hooks, ad-hoc `Promise.all([Task,...])` patterns bypassing `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs`, \"verify\" PASS without precondition checks; PLUS hitting undocumented Claude rate-limit ceiling at ~3 parallel workers because every worker re-loads ~60k context blowing through ITPM. **Success criteria** (8 falsifiable, measure before tag/publish per `feedback_measure_dont_claim.md`): (1) state-preflight envelope schema published as STABLE contract; (2) substrate proves ≥3× speedup on a real fan-out scenario via in-tree proof CLI (measurement, not claim); (3) verify-gate blocks ≥3 distinct state-preflight failure classes (wrong-branch, port-conflict, contract-DRAFT) in `e2e/journeys/`-shape tests with manifest entries; (4) ≥40% token reduction per milestone for execute+verify cycles vs trailing-3 baseline (M52, M54, prior); (5) zero 429 errors at parallelism level D3 declared safe + peak parallelism ≥6 concurrent workers; (6) verify-gate wall-clock ≤ ½ trailing-3 median; (7) Red Team GRUDGING PASS — ≥5 broken patches, all caught (preflight-skip-on-error, parallel-substrate-bypasses-capture, verify-gate-falsy-true, branch-guard-typo, contract-staleness-ignored, brief-staleness-ignored); (8) zero regressions on `npm test` (baseline 2262/2262 unit + 1 documented env-bleed). **Out of scope**: rewriting all 55 command files to call the substrate directly (separate ratchet milestone, pending M55 ship); cross-project preflight/brief propagation via `gsd-t update-all` (follow-up); replacing `bin/gsd-t-worker-dispatch.cjs` or `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs` with the substrate (those are unattended-mode supervisors, distinct surface). **Charter**: `.gsd-t/charters/m55-charter.md`. **Standing directive**: execute through to COMPLETED autonomously; only stop for destructive action, unrecoverable error after 2 fix attempts + debug-loop exit 4, or measurement criteria failure (recalibrate and continue, do not tag). |\n17\t| M52 | Rigorous User-Journey Coverage + Anti-Drift Test Quality | COMPLETE | 3.23.10 | 2 file-disjoint domains. **D1 m52-d1-journey-coverage-tooling** (5 tasks): `bin/journey-coverage.cjs` listener-detector + `bin/journey-coverage-cli.cjs` (`gsd-t check-coverage`) + `scripts/hooks/pre-commit-journey-coverage` + `bin/gsd-t.js` wiring (`installJourneyCoverageHook`, `--install-journey-hook`) + `journey-coverage-contract.md` (manifest schema + listener catalogue + gap rules + exit codes). **D2 m52-d2-journey-specs-and-fixtures** (5 tasks): 12 inaugural `e2e/journeys/*.spec.ts` + `.gsd-t/journey-manifest.json` + 3 real-data NDJSON fixtures under `e2e/fixtures/journeys/` + `replay-helpers.ts` + Red Team \"Test Pass-Through — Journey Edition\" category. **Cross-domain**: only `bin/gsd-t.js` touched by both — D1 only writes it; D2 only reads. **Checkpoints** (`m52-integration-points.md`): C1 D1 publishes `gsd-t check-coverage` + hook installer + STABLE contract → unblocks D2 manifest authoring; C2 D2 lands 12 specs + populated manifest → unblocks verify; C3 Red Team adversarial pass → unblocks complete-milestone. |\n18\t| M50 | Universal Playwright Bootstrap + Deterministic UI Enforcement | COMPLETE | 3.22.10 | 2 domains file-disjoint, single-day in-session build. D1 (5 tasks): `bin/playwright-bootstrap.cjs` (`hasPlaywright`/`detectPackageManager`/`installPlaywright`/`installPlaywrightSync`/`verifyPlaywrightHealth`) + `bin/ui-detection.cjs` (`hasUI`/`detectUIFlavor`) + `bin/gsd-t.js` wiring (init/update-all/doctor/setup-playwright). D2 (10 tasks): spawn-gate in `bin/headless-auto-spawn.cjs` + `scripts/hooks/pre-commit-playwright-gate` + `playwright.config.ts` + 5 E2E viewer specs + doc-ripple + contract flip to STABLE. 62 new unit tests; E2E 8/9 pass (1 documented TEST-M50-001). Goal-Backward PASS (16 REQs). Zero regressions. |\n19\t| M47 | Focused Visualizer Redesign | COMPLETE | 3.21.10 | 2 domains, 12 tasks, single-day in-session build. D1 viewer-redesign (7 tasks): split-pane HTML scaffolding (`#main-stream` + splitter + `#spawn-stream`); 3-section left rail (Main Session / Live / Completed[≤100, newest first, status-badged, collapsible]); dual SSE wiring via new `connectMain(sessionId)` + bottom-pane `connect()`; bucketing logic consumes D2 `status` field; mouse + keyboard splitter (ArrowUp/Down ±5%, Home/End snap); 4 sessionStorage keys (`selectedSpawnId`, `splitterPct`, `completedExpanded`, `rightRailCollapsed`); right-rail collapse toggle; `appendFrame`/`renderFrame` refactored to thread an optional target via module-scope `renderTarget`. D2 server-helpers (5 tasks): 30s-window `status` field on `listInSessionTranscripts`; new `handleMainSession` + `GET /api/main-session` route (path-traversal guarded via `isValidSpawnId`, `Cache-Control: no-store`); `dashboard-server-contract.md` v1.2.0 → v1.3.0; 9 regression tests. Suite 2058/2060 pass (baseline 2045 + 13 M47 new; 2 pre-existing flakes preserved per success-criterion-5). Goal-Backward PASS (0 placeholder patterns). Red Team grudging pass (13 attack vectors, 0 bugs). |\n20\t| M46 | Unattended Iter-Parallel + Worker Fan-Out Completion | COMPLETE | 3.19.00 | 2 domains, single parallel wave, file-disjoint. D1 iter-parallel supervisor (helpers `_runOneIter`/`_computeIterBatchSize`/`_runIterParallel`/`_reconcile` in `bin/gsd-t-unattended.cjs` + `iter-parallel-contract.md` v1.0.0 + `test/m46-d1-iter-parallel.test.js` + `bin/m46-iter-proof.cjs` @ 3.35× speedup). D2 worker-side runDispatch hand-off (new `bin/gsd-t-worker-dispatch.cjs` + `commands/gsd-t-resume.md` additive block + `test/m46-d2-worker-subdispatch.test.js` + `bin/m46-worker-proof.cjs` @ 5.96× speedup + `headless-default-contract.md` v2.0.0 → v2.1.0). Closes five-surface audit gaps 2A (✗ → ✓) and 2B (⚠ → ✓). Iter-parallel scaffold production-default serial; engaged via opt-in `opts.maxIterParallel` — full concurrent-safe work-stealing tracked as backlog #24. |\n21\t| M45 | Conversation-Stream Observability | COMPLETE | 3.18.14 | 2 domains, Wave 1 parallel (file-disjoint test fixture for M44 parallelism). D1 viewer-route-fix (4 tasks, 4/4 tests — `GET /transcripts` now serves `gsd-t-transcript.html` with empty `__SPAWN_ID__`). D2 in-session-conversation-capture (6 tasks, 20/20 tests — new `scripts/hooks/gsd-t-conversation-capture.js`; compact-detector fallback target-selection; viewer left-rail `💬 conversation` badge; `conversation-capture-contract.md` v1.0.0). Red Team found BUG-1 MEDIUM (session_id path-traversal); sanitizer fix + regression test landed. |\n22\t| M44 | Cross-Domain & Cross-Task Parallelism (in-session AND unattended) | COMPLETE | 3.18.10 | 8 of 9 domains. Task-graph reader, `gsd-t parallel` CLI, file-disjointness pr