{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015V14JsC4tQxtyCTR4qMwS3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Context-Brief Contract\n2\t\n3\t> Status: **STABLE**\n4\t> Version: 1.0.0\n5\t> Owner: D4 (`m55-d4-context-brief-generator`)\n6\t> Consumer: D5 (`gsd-t-execute` Step 1 wire-in; subagent prompts read brief path from env)\n7\t> Promoted: 2026-05-09 by D4 build agent.\n8\t\n9\t## Purpose\n10\t\n11\tReplace the 30–60k context re-read every parallel worker performs (CLAUDE.md\n12\t+ contracts + scope + relevant code) with a ≤10 KB / ≤2,500-token JSON\n13\tsnapshot generated once per spawn. Workers grep the brief instead of\n14\tre-walking the repo. The dominant ITPM-relief lever in M55 (charter\n15\tPattern B).\n16\t\n17\t## Library API\n18\t\n19\t```js\n20\tconst { generateBrief } = require('./bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs');\n21\tconst brief = generateBrief({\n22\t  projectDir: '.',\n23\t  kind: 'execute',\n24\t  domain: 'm55-d1-state-precondition-library',\n25\t  spawnId: 'execute-D1-T3-20260509T160000Z',\n26\t});\n27\tfs.writeFileSync(`.gsd-t/briefs/${brief.spawnId}.json`, JSON.stringify(brief, null, 2));\n28\t```\n29\t\n30\t### Public exports\n31\t\n32\t| Export | Type | Purpose |\n33\t|--------|------|---------|\n34\t| `generateBrief(opts)` | `({projectDir, kind, domain, spawnId, strict?, now?}) => Brief` | Pure synchronous brief assembly. |\n35\t| `SCHEMA_VERSION` | `string` | `'1.0.0'`. |\n36\t| `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` | `number` | `10240` (≈2,500 tokens at ~4 chars/token). |\n37\t| `KINDS` | `string[]` | `['design-verify','execute','qa','red-team','scan','verify']`. |\n38\t| `loadKindRegistry()` | `() => KindModule[]` | Directory scan of `bin/gsd-t-context-brief-kinds/`. |\n39\t\n40\tThe library MUST NOT spawn LLMs, network requests, or any subprocess other\n41\tthan read-only `git` invocations executed inside per-kind collectors.\n42\t\n43\t## CLI Form\n44\t\n45\t```\n46\tnode bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs --kind execute --domain m55-d1-... --spawn-id smoke-001 --json\n47\tnode bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs --kind qa --domain m55-d3-... --spawn-id qa-001 --out .gsd-t/briefs/qa-001.json\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\tFlags:\n51\t\n52\t| Flag | Required | Notes |\n53\t|------|----------|-------|\n54\t| `--kind X` | yes | Must be one of `KINDS`. |\n55\t| `--domain Y` | yes for execute/verify/qa/red-team kinds; optional for scan/design-verify | Path-safety: matches `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`. |\n56\t| `--spawn-id Z` | yes | Path-safety: matches `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`. |\n57\t| `--out PATH` | optional | Writes brief to file. Without `--out` the brief prints to stdout. |\n58\t| `--json` | optional | Default. JSON envelope to stdout when `--out` absent. |\n59\t| `--strict` | optional | Fail-closed on missing OPTIONAL sources too. |\n60\t| `--project DIR` | optional | Defaults to `.`. |\n61\t| `--help` | optional | Prints usage. |\n62\t\n63\tExit codes:\n64\t\n65\t| Code | Meaning |\n66\t|------|---------|\n67\t| `0` | Brief generated. |\n68\t| `2` | CLI usage error (bad flag, missing required, path-safety reject). |\n69\t| `4` | Required source missing (fail-closed kinds: qa, red-team, design-verify) OR `--strict` over an optional source OR brief exceeds `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES`. |\n70\t\n71\tThe wrapper around `gsd-t-token-capture.cjs` does not apply (see\n72\t§ captureSpawn Exemption).\n73\t\n74\t## Schema\n75\t\n76\t```json\n77\t{\n78\t  \"schemaVersion\": \"1.0.0\",\n79\t  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-05-09T16:00:00.000Z\",\n80\t  \"spawnId\": \"string\",\n81\t  \"kind\": \"execute|verify|qa|red-team|design-verify|scan\",\n82\t  \"domain\": \"string|null\",\n83\t  \"sourceMtimes\": { \"<repo-relative-path>\": \"ISO8601\" },\n84\t  \"branch\": \"string\",\n85\t  \"contracts\": [\n86\t    { \"path\": \"string\", \"status\": \"STABLE|DRAFT|PROPOSED|UNKNOWN\" }\n87\t  ],\n88\t  \"scope\": {\n89\t    \"owned\": [\"...\"],\n90\t    \"notOwned\": [\"...\"],\n91\t    \"deliverables\": [\"...\"]\n92\t  },\n93\t  \"constraints\": [\"...\"],\n94\t  \"ancillary\": { \"<kind-specific>\": \"...\" }\n95\t}\n96\t```\n97\t\n98\tTop-level keys appear in alphabetical order in serialized output (stable\n99\tkeys). Nested arrays are sorted unless explicitly noted as ordered (e.g.\n100\t`recentCommits` for the `red-team` kind, which is newest-first).\n101\t\n102\t## Hard Token Cap\n103\t\n104\tEvery brief is ≤2,500 tokens (≤`MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` = 10,240 bytes of JSON).\n105\tValidation is enforced in `generateBrief` at write-time:\n106\t\n107\t- If serialized length > `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES`, the library throws an\n108\t  `Error('brief exceeds MAX_BRIEF_BYTES (...)')` and `--out` is NOT\n109\t  written. The CLI returns exit 4.\n110\t- Over-cap is a runtime error, never silent truncation. Kind collectors\n111\t  that risk the cap MUST summarize via `sha256-prefix(8)`, line count,\n112\t  or first-N-line snippet — never inline raw 30 KB contracts.\n113\t\n114\t## Freshness via mtime hash-stamp\n115\t\n116\t`sourceMtimes` records every file the brief depends on, keyed by the path\n117\tthe kind passed to the recorder, with the value set to the file's mtime\n118\tISO string. A consumer regenerates if any `sourceMtimes[path]` mtime is\n119\tnewer than the recorded value. Default behavior is fail-open (`null`\n120\tfield, brief still written) when an optional source is missing; `--strict`\n121\tfails closed (exit 4).\n122\t\n123\t## Idempotent-Join\n124\t\n125\tSame `(projectDir, kind, domain, spawnId, sourceMtimes)` →\n126\tbyte-identical brief output **with the single exception of\n127\t`generatedAt`**. Sort all arrays. Stable JSON keys. Nested objects\n128\tserialized in alphabetical key order. The library exposes a deterministic\n129\tJSON.stringify shim that the test suite uses to assert byte-identical\n130\tre-generation.\n131\t\n132\t## Fail-Open vs Fail-Closed (per kind)\n133\t\n134\t| Kind | Default mode | Required sources |\n135\t|------|--------------|------------------|\n136\t| `execute` | fail-open | none (domain dir absence → brief fields null) |\n137\t| `verify`  | fail-open | none |\n138\t| `scan`    | fail-open | none |\n139\t| `qa`      | fail-CLOSED | `templates/prompts/qa-subagent.md` |\n140\t| `red-team` | fail-CLOSED | `templates/prompts/red-team-subagent.md` |\n141\t| `design-verify` | fail-CLOSED | at least one of `.gsd-t/contracts/design-contract.md` or `.gsd-t/contracts/design/INDEX.md` |\n142\t\n143\t`--strict` upgrades fail-open kinds to fail-closed for any missing\n144\toptional source.\n145\t\n146\t## captureSpawn Exemption\n147\t\n148\tBrief generation is pure (filesystem + read-only git read; never spawns\n149\tLLM children) and is therefore exempt from `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs`\n150\twrapping. This exemption is explicit and locked to this contract — any\n151\tfuture kind collector that triggers an LLM child MUST be rejected during\n152\treview and revert to a synchronous, deterministic implementation (or\n153\tmove to a separate library that does flow through the wrapper).\n154\t\n155\t## Path Safety\n156\t\n157\t`--domain` and `--spawn-id` accept ONLY characters matching\n158\t`^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`. Any input containing `/`, `..`, leading dot,\n159\twhitespace, or other punctuation is rejected with exit code 2 and a\n160\tstructured error to stderr. The library validates these inputs at the\n161\tstart of `generateBrief` and CLI argv parse.\n162\t\n163\t## `.gsd-t/briefs/` is gitignored\n164\t\n165\tBriefs are per-spawn ephemera, not committed artifacts.\n166\t\n167\t- Repo-level `.gitignore` MUST contain a line `.gsd-t/briefs/`.\n168\t- D4 ships `.gsd-t/briefs/.gitignore` containing `*\\n!.gitignore\\n` so\n169\t  the directory exists in-repo but its contents are excluded.\n170\t\n171\t## Kind Registry Shape\n172\t\n173\tEach `bin/gsd-t-context-brief-kinds/{name}.cjs` exports:\n174\t\n175\t```js\n176\tmodule.exports = {\n177\t  name: 'execute',                    // matches filename stem\n178\t  requiresSources: ['templates/.../qa-subagent.md'], // empty array allowed\n179\t  collect(ctx) {\n180\t    // ctx = { projectDir, kind, domain, spawnId, recordSource }\n181\t    // Returns the kind-specific subset {scope, constraints, contracts, ancillary}.\n182\t  },\n183\t};\n184\t```\n185\t\n186\tThe library's `loadKindRegistry()` is a deterministic directory scan —\n187\tadding a new kind is a single-file change. The registry validates\n188\tfilename stem === `name`, that `collect` is a function, and that\n189\t`requiresSources` is an array of strings. Modules failing validation are\n190\tskipped with a structured note (no crash).\n191\t\n192\t## Schema-Version Bump Rules\n193\t\n194\t| Change | Bump |\n195\t|--------|------|\n196\t| Add an optional top-level field that older consumers can ignore | minor (`1.0.0 → 1.1.0`) |\n197\t| Change a default from fail-open to fail-closed for any kind | minor (`1.0.0 → 1.1.0`) |\n198\t| Remove a top-level field | major (`1.0.0 → 2.0.0`) |\n199\t| Change semantics of `sourceMtimes` keys (e.g., absolute vs relative) | major |\n200\t| Bump `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` upward | minor |\n201\t| Lower `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` | major (existing briefs may be invalidated) |\n202\t\n203\t## Promotion to STABLE — locked criteria\n204\t\n205\tD4 promoted v1.0.0 STABLE when ALL of the following held:\n206\t- Library + 6 kind collectors shipped.\n207\t- ≥1 unit test per kind plus envelope/freshness/idempotent-join/path-safety/hard-cap.\n208\t- Charter-aligned schema validated by `test/m55-d4-context-brief.test.js`.\n209\t- `.gsd-t/briefs/` and its `.gitignore` shipped.\n210\t- `npm test` passes with no new regressions.\n211\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7a22423-cc58-497c-b885-89dea884b91e","uuid":"474f5c70-afff-4d45-b15b-ec68fe48758a","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:09:02.007Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/contracts/context-brief-contract.md","content":"# Context-Brief Contract\n\n> Status: **STABLE**\n> Version: 1.0.0\n> Owner: D4 (`m55-d4-context-brief-generator`)\n> Consumer: D5 (`gsd-t-execute` Step 1 wire-in; subagent prompts read brief path from env)\n> Promoted: 2026-05-09 by D4 build agent.\n\n## Purpose\n\nReplace the 30–60k context re-read every parallel worker performs (CLAUDE.md\n+ contracts + scope + relevant code) with a ≤10 KB / ≤2,500-token JSON\nsnapshot generated once per spawn. Workers grep the brief instead of\nre-walking the repo. The dominant ITPM-relief lever in M55 (charter\nPattern B).\n\n## Library API\n\n```js\nconst { generateBrief } = require('./bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs');\nconst brief = generateBrief({\n  projectDir: '.',\n  kind: 'execute',\n  domain: 'm55-d1-state-precondition-library',\n  spawnId: 'execute-D1-T3-20260509T160000Z',\n});\nfs.writeFileSync(`.gsd-t/briefs/${brief.spawnId}.json`, JSON.stringify(brief, null, 2));\n```\n\n### Public exports\n\n| Export | Type | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `generateBrief(opts)` | `({projectDir, kind, domain, spawnId, strict?, now?}) => Brief` | Pure synchronous brief assembly. |\n| `SCHEMA_VERSION` | `string` | `'1.0.0'`. |\n| `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` | `number` | `10240` (≈2,500 tokens at ~4 chars/token). |\n| `KINDS` | `string[]` | `['design-verify','execute','qa','red-team','scan','verify']`. |\n| `loadKindRegistry()` | `() => KindModule[]` | Directory scan of `bin/gsd-t-context-brief-kinds/`. |\n\nThe library MUST NOT spawn LLMs, network requests, or any subprocess other\nthan read-only `git` invocations executed inside per-kind collectors.\n\n## CLI Form\n\n```\nnode bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs --kind execute --domain m55-d1-... --spawn-id smoke-001 --json\nnode bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs --kind qa --domain m55-d3-... --spawn-id qa-001 --out .gsd-t/briefs/qa-001.json\n```\n\nFlags:\n\n| Flag | Required | Notes |\n|------|----------|-------|\n| `--kind X` | yes | Must be one of `KINDS`. |\n| `--domain Y` | yes for execute/verify/qa/red-team kinds; optional for scan/design-verify | Path-safety: matches `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`. |\n| `--spawn-id Z` | yes | Path-safety: matches `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`. |\n| `--out PATH` | optional | Writes brief to file. Without `--out` the brief prints to stdout. |\n| `--json` | optional | Default. JSON envelope to stdout when `--out` absent. |\n| `--strict` | optional | Fail-closed on missing OPTIONAL sources too. |\n| `--project DIR` | optional | Defaults to `.`. |\n| `--help` | optional | Prints usage. |\n\nExit codes:\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `0` | Brief generated. |\n| `2` | CLI usage error (bad flag, missing required, path-safety reject). |\n| `4` | Required source missing (fail-closed kinds: qa, red-team, design-verify) OR `--strict` over an optional source OR brief exceeds `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES`. |\n\nThe wrapper around `gsd-t-token-capture.cjs` does not apply (see\n§ captureSpawn Exemption).\n\n## Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schemaVersion\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-05-09T16:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"spawnId\": \"string\",\n  \"kind\": \"execute|verify|qa|red-team|design-verify|scan\",\n  \"domain\": \"string|null\",\n  \"sourceMtimes\": { \"<repo-relative-path>\": \"ISO8601\" },\n  \"branch\": \"string\",\n  \"contracts\": [\n    { \"path\": \"string\", \"status\": \"STABLE|DRAFT|PROPOSED|UNKNOWN\" }\n  ],\n  \"scope\": {\n    \"owned\": [\"...\"],\n    \"notOwned\": [\"...\"],\n    \"deliverables\": [\"...\"]\n  },\n  \"constraints\": [\"...\"],\n  \"ancillary\": { \"<kind-specific>\": \"...\" }\n}\n```\n\nTop-level keys appear in alphabetical order in serialized output (stable\nkeys). Nested arrays are sorted unless explicitly noted as ordered (e.g.\n`recentCommits` for the `red-team` kind, which is newest-first).\n\n## Hard Token Cap\n\nEvery brief is ≤2,500 tokens (≤`MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` = 10,240 bytes of JSON).\nValidation is enforced in `generateBrief` at write-time:\n\n- If serialized length > `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES`, the library throws an\n  `Error('brief exceeds MAX_BRIEF_BYTES (...)')` and `--out` is NOT\n  written. The CLI returns exit 4.\n- Over-cap is a runtime error, never silent truncation. Kind collectors\n  that risk the cap MUST summarize via `sha256-prefix(8)`, line count,\n  or first-N-line snippet — never inline raw 30 KB contracts.\n\n## Freshness via mtime hash-stamp\n\n`sourceMtimes` records every file the brief depends on, keyed by the path\nthe kind passed to the recorder, with the value set to the file's mtime\nISO string. A consumer regenerates if any `sourceMtimes[path]` mtime is\nnewer than the recorded value. Default behavior is fail-open (`null`\nfield, brief still written) when an optional source is missing; `--strict`\nfails closed (exit 4).\n\n## Idempotent-Join\n\nSame `(projectDir, kind, domain, spawnId, sourceMtimes)` →\nbyte-identical brief output **with the single exception of\n`generatedAt`**. Sort all arrays. Stable JSON keys. Nested objects\nserialized in alphabetical key order. The library exposes a deterministic\nJSON.stringify shim that the test suite uses to assert byte-identical\nre-generation.\n\n## Fail-Open vs Fail-Closed (per kind)\n\n| Kind | Default mode | Required sources |\n|------|--------------|------------------|\n| `execute` | fail-open | none (domain dir absence → brief fields null) |\n| `verify`  | fail-open | none |\n| `scan`    | fail-open | none |\n| `qa`      | fail-CLOSED | `templates/prompts/qa-subagent.md` |\n| `red-team` | fail-CLOSED | `templates/prompts/red-team-subagent.md` |\n| `design-verify` | fail-CLOSED | at least one of `.gsd-t/contracts/design-contract.md` or `.gsd-t/contracts/design/INDEX.md` |\n\n`--strict` upgrades fail-open kinds to fail-closed for any missing\noptional source.\n\n## captureSpawn Exemption\n\nBrief generation is pure (filesystem + read-only git read; never spawns\nLLM children) and is therefore exempt from `bin/gsd-t-token-capture.cjs`\nwrapping. This exemption is explicit and locked to this contract — any\nfuture kind collector that triggers an LLM child MUST be rejected during\nreview and revert to a synchronous, deterministic implementation (or\nmove to a separate library that does flow through the wrapper).\n\n## Path Safety\n\n`--domain` and `--spawn-id` accept ONLY characters matching\n`^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`. Any input containing `/`, `..`, leading dot,\nwhitespace, or other punctuation is rejected with exit code 2 and a\nstructured error to stderr. The library validates these inputs at the\nstart of `generateBrief` and CLI argv parse.\n\n## `.gsd-t/briefs/` is gitignored\n\nBriefs are per-spawn ephemera, not committed artifacts.\n\n- Repo-level `.gitignore` MUST contain a line `.gsd-t/briefs/`.\n- D4 ships `.gsd-t/briefs/.gitignore` containing `*\\n!.gitignore\\n` so\n  the directory exists in-repo but its contents are excluded.\n\n## Kind Registry Shape\n\nEach `bin/gsd-t-context-brief-kinds/{name}.cjs` exports:\n\n```js\nmodule.exports = {\n  name: 'execute',                    // matches filename stem\n  requiresSources: ['templates/.../qa-subagent.md'], // empty array allowed\n  collect(ctx) {\n    // ctx = { projectDir, kind, domain, spawnId, recordSource }\n    // Returns the kind-specific subset {scope, constraints, contracts, ancillary}.\n  },\n};\n```\n\nThe library's `loadKindRegistry()` is a deterministic directory scan —\nadding a new kind is a single-file change. The registry validates\nfilename stem === `name`, that `collect` is a function, and that\n`requiresSources` is an array of strings. Modules failing validation are\nskipped with a structured note (no crash).\n\n## Schema-Version Bump Rules\n\n| Change | Bump |\n|--------|------|\n| Add an optional top-level field that older consumers can ignore | minor (`1.0.0 → 1.1.0`) |\n| Change a default from fail-open to fail-closed for any kind | minor (`1.0.0 → 1.1.0`) |\n| Remove a top-level field | major (`1.0.0 → 2.0.0`) |\n| Change semantics of `sourceMtimes` keys (e.g., absolute vs relative) | major |\n| Bump `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` upward | minor |\n| Lower `MAX_BRIEF_BYTES` | major (existing briefs may be invalidated) |\n\n## Promotion to STABLE — locked criteria\n\nD4 promoted v1.0.0 STABLE when ALL of the following held:\n- Library + 6 kind collectors shipped.\n- ≥1 unit test per kind plus envelope/freshness/idempotent-join/path-safety/hard-cap.\n- Charter-aligned schema validated by `test/m55-d4-context-brief.test.js`.\n- `.gsd-t/briefs/` and its `.gitignore` shipped.\n- `npm test` passes with no new regressions.\n","numLines":211,"startLine":1,"totalLines":211}}}
