{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P2VVaKGVsa2qq47Y5Utdu8","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Verify-Gate Contract\n2\t\n3\t> Status: **PROPOSED** — partition stub. D5 (`m55-d5-verify-gate-and-wirein`) promotes to STABLE during execute.\n4\t> Version: 0.1.0 (stub) → 1.0.0 (STABLE target)\n5\t> Owner: D5\n6\t> Consumer: `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` Step 2 (LLM judges the ≤500-token summary)\n7\t\n8\t## Purpose\n9\t\n10\tTwo-track gate that executes BOTH:\n11\t- **Track 1** — D1's state-preflight envelope (hard-fail on any `severity: error` check)\n12\t- **Track 2** — D2's parallel-CLI substrate fans out typecheck / lint / tests / dead-code / secrets / complexity using off-the-shelf CLIs\n13\t\n14\tReturns a ≤500-token JSON summary an LLM judges. Raw worker output stays on disk.\n15\t\n16\t## Library API (target)\n17\t\n18\t```js\n19\tconst { runVerifyGate } = require('./bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs');\n20\tconst result = await runVerifyGate({\n21\t  projectDir: '.',\n22\t  preflightChecks: undefined,            // default = all D1 built-ins\n23\t  parallelTrack: undefined,              // default = all 6 CLIs (with skip-if-not-installed)\n24\t  maxConcurrency: undefined,             // default = read .gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json::recommended.peakConcurrency, fallback 2\n25\t  summaryTokenCap: 500\n26\t});\n27\t// result: { ok, schemaVersion, track1: {...preflight envelope...}, track2: {...summary...}, summary: {...≤500 tokens...}, llmJudgePromptHint, meta: { runId, generatedAt } }\n28\t```\n29\t\n30\t## CLI Form (target)\n31\t\n32\t```\n33\tgsd-t verify-gate --json\n34\tgsd-t verify-gate --skip-track1\n35\tgsd-t verify-gate --max-concurrency 4 --json\n36\t```\n37\t\n38\t## Two-Track Hard-Fail\n39\t\n40\t`top-level ok = track1.ok && track2.ok`. Both tracks always run (unless `--skip-track1` or `--skip-track2`); both report. The LLM judge sees the summary and renders a verdict; the gate's `ok` is purely deterministic.\n41\t\n42\t## ≤500-Token Summary\n43\t\n44\tEach Track 2 worker contributes a head-and-tail snippet of stdout + stderr (configurable per CLI). Total summary ≤500 tokens. Raw output stored at `.gsd-t/verify-gate/{runId}/{workerId}.{stdout,stderr}.log` — human-only inspection.\n45\t\n46\t## Off-the-Shelf CLIs\n47\t\n48\t| Job | CLI (default) | If not installed |\n49\t|-----|--------------|-----------------|\n50\t| typecheck | `tsc --noEmit` (or detected) | `skipped: true, reason: \"not installed\"` |\n51\t| lint | `biome check` / `ruff check` (detected) | `skipped: true` |\n52\t| tests | detected runner | `skipped: true` |\n53\t| dead-code | `knip` | `skipped: true` |\n54\t| secrets | `gitleaks detect --no-git -v` | `skipped: true` |\n55\t| complexity | `scc` or `lizard` | `skipped: true` |\n56\t\n57\tD5 NEVER auto-installs.\n58\t\n59\t## Idempotent Re-Runs\n60\t\n61\tSame source state → byte-identical `track1` + `track2.summary` (modulo timestamps in `meta`).\n62\t\n63\t## D3 Map Defensive Default\n64\t\n65\tIf `.gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json` doesn't exist, log warning + use `maxConcurrency=2`.\n66\t\n67\t## Schema (target — D5 finalizes)\n68\t\n69\t```json\n70\t{\n71\t  \"schemaVersion\": \"1.0.0\",\n72\t  \"ok\": true,\n73\t  \"track1\": { /* D1 preflight envelope verbatim */ },\n74\t  \"track2\": {\n75\t    \"workers\": [\n76\t      { \"id\": \"tsc\", \"ok\": true, \"exitCode\": 0, \"durationMs\": 1234, \"skipped\": false, \"summarySnippet\": \"...\" }\n77\t    ],\n78\t    \"wallClockMs\": 5678,\n79\t    \"ok\": true\n80\t  },\n81\t  \"summary\": { /* ≤500-token JSON for LLM */ },\n82\t  \"llmJudgePromptHint\": \"Render a verdict on the summary above. PASS / FAIL.\",\n83\t  \"meta\": { \"runId\": \"verify-gate-...Z\", \"generatedAt\": \"ISO8601\" }\n84\t}\n85\t```\n86\t\n87\t## SC3 Failure Classes (D5 must produce 3 e2e/journeys specs)\n88\t\n89\t| Failure class | Spec | Expected behavior |\n90\t|---------------|------|-------------------|\n91\t| Wrong branch | `e2e/journeys/verify-gate-blocks-wrong-branch.spec.ts` | `track1.checks[branch-guard].ok=false`; gate exits non-zero |\n92\t| Port conflict | `e2e/journeys/verify-gate-blocks-port-conflict.spec.ts` | `track1.checks[ports-free].ok=false`; gate exits non-zero |\n93\t| Contract DRAFT | `e2e/journeys/verify-gate-blocks-contract-draft.spec.ts` | `track1.checks[contracts-stable].ok=false`; gate exits non-zero |\n94\t\n95\t## Promotion to STABLE\n96\t\n97\tD5 promotes to v1.0.0 STABLE when:\n98\t- Library + judge companion shipped\n99\t- 3 wire-in assertion tests pass\n100\t- 3 e2e/journeys SC3 specs pass + manifest entries land\n101\t- Doc ripple complete (every surface in D5 scope's wire-in table)\n102\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7a22423-cc58-497c-b885-89dea884b91e","uuid":"3c0d40ea-ca20-4de0-9cb1-394e22ab71ee","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:09:24.917Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/contracts/verify-gate-contract.md","content":"# Verify-Gate Contract\n\n> Status: **PROPOSED** — partition stub. D5 (`m55-d5-verify-gate-and-wirein`) promotes to STABLE during execute.\n> Version: 0.1.0 (stub) → 1.0.0 (STABLE target)\n> Owner: D5\n> Consumer: `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` Step 2 (LLM judges the ≤500-token summary)\n\n## Purpose\n\nTwo-track gate that executes BOTH:\n- **Track 1** — D1's state-preflight envelope (hard-fail on any `severity: error` check)\n- **Track 2** — D2's parallel-CLI substrate fans out typecheck / lint / tests / dead-code / secrets / complexity using off-the-shelf CLIs\n\nReturns a ≤500-token JSON summary an LLM judges. Raw worker output stays on disk.\n\n## Library API (target)\n\n```js\nconst { runVerifyGate } = require('./bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs');\nconst result = await runVerifyGate({\n  projectDir: '.',\n  preflightChecks: undefined,            // default = all D1 built-ins\n  parallelTrack: undefined,              // default = all 6 CLIs (with skip-if-not-installed)\n  maxConcurrency: undefined,             // default = read .gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json::recommended.peakConcurrency, fallback 2\n  summaryTokenCap: 500\n});\n// result: { ok, schemaVersion, track1: {...preflight envelope...}, track2: {...summary...}, summary: {...≤500 tokens...}, llmJudgePromptHint, meta: { runId, generatedAt } }\n```\n\n## CLI Form (target)\n\n```\ngsd-t verify-gate --json\ngsd-t verify-gate --skip-track1\ngsd-t verify-gate --max-concurrency 4 --json\n```\n\n## Two-Track Hard-Fail\n\n`top-level ok = track1.ok && track2.ok`. Both tracks always run (unless `--skip-track1` or `--skip-track2`); both report. The LLM judge sees the summary and renders a verdict; the gate's `ok` is purely deterministic.\n\n## ≤500-Token Summary\n\nEach Track 2 worker contributes a head-and-tail snippet of stdout + stderr (configurable per CLI). Total summary ≤500 tokens. Raw output stored at `.gsd-t/verify-gate/{runId}/{workerId}.{stdout,stderr}.log` — human-only inspection.\n\n## Off-the-Shelf CLIs\n\n| Job | CLI (default) | If not installed |\n|-----|--------------|-----------------|\n| typecheck | `tsc --noEmit` (or detected) | `skipped: true, reason: \"not installed\"` |\n| lint | `biome check` / `ruff check` (detected) | `skipped: true` |\n| tests | detected runner | `skipped: true` |\n| dead-code | `knip` | `skipped: true` |\n| secrets | `gitleaks detect --no-git -v` | `skipped: true` |\n| complexity | `scc` or `lizard` | `skipped: true` |\n\nD5 NEVER auto-installs.\n\n## Idempotent Re-Runs\n\nSame source state → byte-identical `track1` + `track2.summary` (modulo timestamps in `meta`).\n\n## D3 Map Defensive Default\n\nIf `.gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json` doesn't exist, log warning + use `maxConcurrency=2`.\n\n## Schema (target — D5 finalizes)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schemaVersion\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"track1\": { /* D1 preflight envelope verbatim */ },\n  \"track2\": {\n    \"workers\": [\n      { \"id\": \"tsc\", \"ok\": true, \"exitCode\": 0, \"durationMs\": 1234, \"skipped\": false, \"summarySnippet\": \"...\" }\n    ],\n    \"wallClockMs\": 5678,\n    \"ok\": true\n  },\n  \"summary\": { /* ≤500-token JSON for LLM */ },\n  \"llmJudgePromptHint\": \"Render a verdict on the summary above. PASS / FAIL.\",\n  \"meta\": { \"runId\": \"verify-gate-...Z\", \"generatedAt\": \"ISO8601\" }\n}\n```\n\n## SC3 Failure Classes (D5 must produce 3 e2e/journeys specs)\n\n| Failure class | Spec | Expected behavior |\n|---------------|------|-------------------|\n| Wrong branch | `e2e/journeys/verify-gate-blocks-wrong-branch.spec.ts` | `track1.checks[branch-guard].ok=false`; gate exits non-zero |\n| Port conflict | `e2e/journeys/verify-gate-blocks-port-conflict.spec.ts` | `track1.checks[ports-free].ok=false`; gate exits non-zero |\n| Contract DRAFT | `e2e/journeys/verify-gate-blocks-contract-draft.spec.ts` | `track1.checks[contracts-stable].ok=false`; gate exits non-zero |\n\n## Promotion to STABLE\n\nD5 promotes to v1.0.0 STABLE when:\n- Library + judge companion shipped\n- 3 wire-in assertion tests pass\n- 3 e2e/journeys SC3 specs pass + manifest entries land\n- Doc ripple complete (every surface in D5 scope's wire-in table)\n","numLines":102,"startLine":1,"totalLines":102}}}
