{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SnGpCcdrj1KWxMcijTPJco","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Red Team Subagent Prompt — Adversarial QA (per-domain)\n2\t\n3\tYou are a Red Team QA adversary. Your job is to BREAK the code that was just written for this domain. You operate with inverted incentives — your value is measured by REAL bugs found, not tests passed.\n4\t\n5\t## Hard Rules\n6\t\n7\t- **Bugs found = value.** A short attack list is failure.\n8\t- **False positives DESTROY your credibility.** Never report something you have not reproduced. A bug is `I did X, expected Y, got Z` with proof.\n9\t- Style opinions are NOT bugs. Theoretical concerns are NOT bugs.\n10\t- You are done ONLY when you have exhausted every category below — either find a real bug or document exactly what you tried and why it didn't break."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7a22423-cc58-497c-b885-89dea884b91e","uuid":"a70f8d58-4f50-46af-a0aa-ccb5e8a8b091","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:19:20.938Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/templates/prompts/red-team-subagent.md","content":"# Red Team Subagent Prompt — Adversarial QA (per-domain)\n\nYou are a Red Team QA adversary. Your job is to BREAK the code that was just written for this domain. You operate with inverted incentives — your value is measured by REAL bugs found, not tests passed.\n\n## Hard Rules\n\n- **Bugs found = value.** A short attack list is failure.\n- **False positives DESTROY your credibility.** Never report something you have not reproduced. A bug is `I did X, expected Y, got Z` with proof.\n- Style opinions are NOT bugs. Theoretical concerns are NOT bugs.\n- You are done ONLY when you have exhausted every category below — either find a real bug or document exactly what you tried and why it didn't break.","numLines":10,"startLine":1,"totalLines":98}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Rs88roEjSMm4iYmwY71qec","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UY2xuieCTffLznVxk7ijvu","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/templates/prompts/red-team-subagent.md","old_string":"# Red Team Subagent Prompt — Adversarial QA (per-domain)\n\nYou are a Red Team QA adversary. Your job is to BREAK the code that was just written for this domain. You operate with inverted incentives — your value is measured by REAL bugs found, not tests passed.","new_string":"# Red Team Subagent Prompt — Adversarial QA (per-domain)\n\nYou are a Red Team QA adversary. Your job is to BREAK the code that was just written for this domain. You operate with inverted incentives — your value is measured by REAL bugs found, not tests passed.\n\n<!-- M55-D5: brief-first rule -->\n**Brief first.** If you're about to grep, read, or run a test, check the brief first at `$BRIEF_PATH` (a ≤2,500-token JSON snapshot of CLAUDE.md + contracts + scope + constraints + recent commits, generated by `bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs --kind red-team`). The brief identifies high-risk surfaces, recent diffs, and contract status — your starting attack surface. The brief replaces the 30–60k context re-read every parallel worker would otherwise perform. If `$BRIEF_PATH` is unset or the file is missing, fall back to the legacy read-everything pattern, but log a note so the orchestrator can see the gap."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":170540,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":397},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7a22423-cc58-497c-b885-89dea884b91e","uuid":"3a275fa3-0f48-4f1c-8699