{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UXdHEoD3ABrYR2Fx3yxaUJ","type":"tool_result","content":"451\t## Pre-Commit Gate (MANDATORY)\n452\t\n453\tNEVER commit code without running this checklist. This is not optional.\n454\t\n455\t```\n456\tBEFORE EVERY COMMIT:\n457\t  ├── Am I on the correct branch?\n458\t  │     CHECK → Run `git branch --show-current`\n459\t  │     Compare against \"Expected branch\" in project CLAUDE.md\n460\t  │     WRONG BRANCH → STOP. Do NOT commit. Switch to the correct branch first.\n461\t  │     No guard set → Proceed (but warn user to set one)\n462\t  ├── Did I create or change an API endpoint or response shape?\n463\t  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/contracts/api-contract.md\n464\t  │     YES → Update Swagger/OpenAPI spec (see API Documentation Guard below)\n465\t  │     YES → Verify Swagger URL is in CLAUDE.md and README.md\n466\t  ├── Did I change the database schema?\n467\t  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/contracts/schema-contract.md AND docs/schema.md\n468\t  ├── Did I add/change a UI component interface?\n469\t  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/contracts/component-contract.md\n470\t  ├── Did I add new files or directories?\n471\t  │     YES → Update the owning domain's scope.md\n472\t  ├── Did I implement or change a requirement?\n473\t  │     YES → Update docs/requirements.md (mark complete or revise)\n474\t  ├── Did I add/change/remove a component or change data flow?\n475\t  │     YES → Update docs/architecture.md\n476\t  ├── Did I modify any document, script, or code file?\n477\t  │     YES → Add timestamped entry to .gsd-t/progress.md Decision Log\n478\t  │     Format: `- YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM: {what was done} — {brief context or result}`\n479\t  │     This includes ALL file-modifying activities:\n480\t  │       project, feature, scan, gap-analysis, milestone, partition, discuss,\n481\t  │       plan, impact, execute, test-sync, integrate, verify, complete-milestone,\n482\t  │       wave, quick, debug, promote-debt, populate, setup, init, init-scan-setup,\n483\t  │       backlog-add/edit/move/remove/promote/settings, and any manual code changes\n484\t  ├── Did I make an architectural or design decision?\n485\t  │     YES → Also include decision rationale in the progress.md entry\n486\t  ├── Did I discover or fix tech debt?\n487\t  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/techdebt.md\n488\t  ├── Did I establish a pattern future work should follow?\n489\t  │     YES → Update CLAUDE.md or domain constraints.md\n490\t  ├── Did I add/change tests?\n491\t  │     YES → Verify test names and paths are referenced in requirements\n492\t  ├── Did I change UI, routes, or user flows?\n493\t  │     YES → Update affected E2E test specs (Playwright/Cypress)\n494\t  └── Did I run the affected tests?\n495\t        YES → Verify they pass. NO → Run them now.\n496\t```\n497\t\n498\tIf ANY answer is YES and the doc is NOT updated, update it BEFORE committing. No exceptions.\n499\t\n500\t## Document Ripple Completion Gate (MANDATORY)\n501\t\n502\t**NEVER report a task as \"done\" or present a summary until ALL downstream documents are updated.** This is not optional.\n503\t\n504\tWhen a change affects multiple files (e.g., a new standard that applies across command files, a renamed API, a new convention), you MUST:\n505\t\n506\t1. **Identify the full blast radius BEFORE starting**: List every file that needs the change\n507\t2. **Complete ALL updates in one pass**: Do not update 3 of 8 files and then present a summary\n508\t3. **Run the Pre-Commit Gate on the COMPLETE changeset**: Not on a partial subset\n509\t4. **Only THEN report completion**\n510\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7a22423-cc58-497c-b885-89dea884b91e","uuid":"ccaa1137-d6fa-4055-a8de-05fe3c5b883d","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:28:38.592Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/.claude/CLAUDE.md","content":"## Pre-Commit Gate (MANDATORY)\n\nNEVER commit code without running this checklist. This is not optional.\n\n```\nBEFORE EVERY COMMIT:\n  ├── Am I on the correct branch?\n  │     CHECK → Run `git branch --show-current`\n  │     Compare against \"Expected branch\" in project CLAUDE.md\n  │     WRONG BRANCH → STOP. Do NOT commit. Switch to the correct branch first.\n  │     No guard set → Proceed (but warn user to set one)\n  ├── Did I create or change an API endpoint or response shape?\n  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/contracts/api-contract.md\n  │     YES → Update Swagger/OpenAPI spec (see API Documentation Guard below)\n  │     YES → Verify Swagger URL is in CLAUDE.md and README.md\n  ├── Did I change the database schema?\n  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/contracts/schema-contract.md AND docs/schema.md\n  ├── Did I add/change a UI component interface?\n  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/contracts/component-contract.md\n  ├── Did I add new files or directories?\n  │     YES → Update the owning domain's scope.md\n  ├── Did I implement or change a requirement?\n  │     YES → Update docs/requirements.md (mark complete or revise)\n  ├── Did I add/change/remove a component or change data flow?\n  │     YES → Update docs/architecture.md\n  ├── Did I modify any document, script, or code file?\n  │     YES → Add timestamped entry to .gsd-t/progress.md Decision Log\n  │     Format: `- YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM: {what was done} — {brief context or result}`\n  │     This includes ALL file-modifying activities:\n  │       project, feature, scan, gap-analysis, milestone, partition, discuss,\n  │       plan, impact, execute, test-sync, integrate, verify, complete-milestone,\n  │       wave, quick, debug, promote-debt, populate, setup, init, init-scan-setup,\n  │       backlog-add/edit/move/remove/promote/settings, and any manual code changes\n  ├── Did I make an architectural or design decision?\n  │     YES → Also include decision rationale in the progress.md entry\n  ├── Did I discover or fix tech debt?\n  │     YES → Update .gsd-t/techdebt.md\n  ├── Did I establish a pattern future work should follow?\n  │     YES → Update CLAUDE.md or domain constraints.md\n  ├── Did I add/change tests?\n  │     YES → Verify test names and paths are referenced in requirements\n  ├── Did I change UI, routes, or user flows?\n  │     YES → Update affected E2E test specs (Playwright/Cypress)\n  └── Did I run the affected tests?\n        YES → Verify they pass. NO → Run them now.\n```\n\nIf ANY answer is YES and the doc is NOT updated, update it BEFORE committing. No exceptions.\n\n## Document Ripple Completion Gate (MANDATORY)\n\n**NEVER report a task as \"done\" or present a summary until ALL downstream documents are updated.** This is not optional.\n\nWhen a change affects multiple files (e.g., a new standard that applies across command files, a renamed API, a new convention), you MUST:\n\n1. **Identify the full blast radius BEFORE starting**: List every file that needs the change\n2. **Complete ALL updates in one pass**: Do not update 3 of 8 files and then present a summary\n3. **Run the Pre-Commit Gate on the COMPLETE changeset**: Not on a partial subset\n4. **Only THEN report completion**\n","numLines":60,"startLine":451,"totalLines":699}}}
