jectDir(payload)` fell through to `_walkUpForProject(process.cwd())` when `GSD_T_PROJECT_DIR` was unset and `payload.cwd` was absent. `process.cwd()` for a Claude Code Stop/UserPromptSubmit hook is the directory the user launched `claude` from. When two parallel Claude Code sessions ran in different projects (`/Users/david/projects/GSD-T` and `/Users/david/projects/Move-Zoom-Recordings-to-GDrive`), the SAME node-runtime hook process resolved to whichever project the hook inherited via cwd — frames cross-talked. Concrete misroute: GSD-T orchestrator's NDJSON written into `Move-Zoom-Recordings-to-GDrive/.gsd-t/transcripts/in-session-800d4b3b-….ndjson` (verified 2026-05-07 11:30 — content was THIS session's banners, file was the wrong project's transcripts dir). **Fix** (2 new private fns + reordered `_resolveProjectDir`): `_slugFromTranscriptPath` extracts the directory-name slug from `~/.claude/projects/{slug}/{sid}.jsonl`; rejects paths outside that root. `_slugToProjectDir` DFS-walks the filesystem from `/`, greedily consuming `-`-separated tokens as directory names; first leaf where `.gsd-t/` exists wins. Disambiguates literal-hyphen project names (`Move-Zoom-Recordings-to-GDrive`) by consulting the disk — disk is the oracle. Rejects slugs containing `..`, `/`, `\\\\`, `\\0`, or not starting with `-`. New priority: env → transcript_path slug → `payload.cwd` → cwd walk-up. Walk-up emits a one-line stderr warning so future misroutes are diagnosable. **Reproduction-first**: wrote `test/m53b-conversation-routing.test.js` BEFORE touching the hook — confirmed the failing scenario, then fixed. **Tests** (`test/m53b-conversation-routing.test.js`, new, 16 cases): happy-path slug-decode beats wrong cwd, parallel-session no-cross-talk, literal-hyphen disambiguation, non-GSD-T target → fallthrough, path-traversal slug rejection, env-priority preservation, UserPromptSubmit also routes by transcript_path, plus 8 unit-level helper tests (slug rejection: not starting with `-`, co